- Page 1: the sentence starting with \'93Over the years\'94 does not seem to have a verb, e.g. \'93has been added\'94 could work.\
- Page 2: \'93as a model finding problems\'94 -> \'93as model finding problems\'94\strike0\striked0 \
\strike \strikec0 - Page 3: \'93but a partial interpretation can be used [\'85] but\'94, I think \'93while a partial\'85\'94 would be better to avoid repeating \'93but\'94.\strike0\striked0 \
\strike \strikec0 - Section 2.2, page 4: the sentence \'93Formulae can be evaluated [\'85] \'85\'94 does not connect semantically with the list after it, maybe some words are missing?\strike0\striked0 \
\strike \strikec0 - Last sentence on page 4 lacks a full stop.\
- Section 5: \'93very many\'94 -> \'93several\'94, \'93numerous\'94?\strike0\striked0 \
